## Accessibility Implementation (Web Accessibility - a11y)

### Skip Navigation and Focus Management
- **MUST implement skip links** to main content on every page
- **MUST manage focus** properly during route transitions
- **SHOULD provide keyboard navigation** for all interactive elements
- **Rationale**: Skip links allow users with assistive technology to bypass repetitive navigation, and proper focus management ensures users don't lose their place when content changes
- **Examples**:
  ```vue
  <!-- ✅ Good - Skip link implementation in App.vue -->
  <template>
    <div id="app">
      <span ref="backToTop" tabindex="-1" />
      <ul class="skip-links">
        <li>
          <a href="#main" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
      
      <AppNavigation />
      
      <main id="main" role="main" aria-labelledby="main-title">
        <RouterView />
      </main>
    </div>
  </template>
  
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref, watch } from 'vue';
  import { useRoute } from 'vue-router';
  
  const route = useRoute();
  const backToTop = ref<HTMLElement>();
  
  // ✅ Good - Reset focus on route change
  watch(
    () => route.path,
    () => {
      backToTop.value?.focus();
    }
  );
  </script>
  
  <style>
  .skip-link {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    background: white;
    padding: 0.5em 1em;
    opacity: 0;
    z-index: 1000;
  }
  
  .skip-link:focus {
    opacity: 1;
  }
  </style>
  ```

### Semantic HTML Structure and Landmarks
- **MUST use proper heading hierarchy** (h1-h6 in logical order)
- **MUST implement ARIA landmarks** for page sections
- **MUST NOT skip heading levels** within content sections
- **Examples**:
  ```vue
  <template>
    <!-- ✅ Good - Proper semantic structure -->
    <div class="page-layout">
      <header role="banner">
        <h1>My Application</h1>
        <nav role="navigation" aria-label="Main navigation">
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/home">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
          </ul>
        </nav>
      </header>
      
      <main role="main" aria-labelledby="page-title">
        <h1 id="page-title">{{ pageTitle }}</h1>
        
        <section aria-labelledby="section-1-title">
          <h2 id="section-1-title">First Section</h2>
          <h3>Subsection A</h3>
          <p>Content...</p>
        </section>
      </main>
      
      <footer role="contentinfo">
        <p>&copy; 2024 My Application</p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </template>
  ```

### Accessible Form Implementation
- **MUST associate labels with form controls** using explicit labeling
- **MUST provide clear instructions** for form fields
- **MUST implement proper error handling** with ARIA attributes
- **SHOULD avoid placeholders** as primary labels
- **Examples**:
  ```vue
  <template>
    <form @submit.prevent="handleSubmit">
      <fieldset>
        <legend>User Information</legend>
        
        <div class="form-group">
          <label for="firstName">First Name (required):</label>
          <input
            id="firstName"
            v-model="form.firstName"
            type="text"
            required
            :aria-invalid="errors.firstName ? 'true' : 'false'"
            :aria-describedby="errors.firstName ? 'firstName-error' : undefined"
          />
          <p
            v-if="errors.firstName"
            id="firstName-error"
            class="error-message"
            role="alert"
          >
            {{ errors.firstName }}
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <button type="submit" :disabled="isSubmitting">
          {{ isSubmitting ? 'Submitting...' : 'Submit' }}
        </button>
      </fieldset>
    </form>
  </template>
  ```

*Reference: [Vue.js Accessibility Best Practices](https://vuejs.org/guide/best-practices/accessibility.html)*
